        <mxCell id="ACs7U7gOFgD1ok9pQ7hg-263" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=20;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;fontColor=#333333;fontSize=10;align=left;" value="&lt;div&gt;valid_from and valid_to represent the time when the row was considered current.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;valid_id holds the atemporal identifier of given sequence of temporal rows. While the actual PK must change every version, valid_id should stay the same through many different versions of the same data.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Temporal Update: First duplicate the row with valid_to equal to current time. Then apply the changes to the original field and update valid_from to current time.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Soft Delete: Simply set valid_to to current time.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
